<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFF9647F47D62FCAFEC8FCCD" blockId="6.[151,1437,698,1604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F47D62FCAFF77FD55" bold="true" box="[151,225,698,724]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Head.</emphasis>
Labrum large, as wide as long, anterior angles rounded, apex between angles slightly emarginate. Maxillary palpomere 4 roundly dilate from middle to apex, inflexed medially and medial surface with distinct, deep puncture, roundly narrowed at apex. Ligula elongate, narrow and tapering towards apex with two elongate apical setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30A949AFFF9647F47842E2AFDB2FB5D" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFF9647F47842E2AFB37FC6D" blockId="6.[151,1437,698,1604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F47842E2AFEDDFCF5" bold="true" box="[197,331,858,884]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Pronotum.</emphasis>
Apical angles projected and rounded; surface densely punctate and pubescent; anterior and posterior transverse sulci shallow; lateral margin explanate and reflexed; posterior angles weakly reflexed and blunt at apex; basal foveae deep and wide, extended forward as deep lateral furrows; lateral margins weakly sinuate anterior to posterior angles; base distinctly oblique laterally, narrower than apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFF9647F47842E8AFE77FBBD" blockId="6.[151,1437,698,1604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F47842E8AFE8AFB95" bold="true" box="[197,284,1018,1044]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Elytra.</emphasis>
Apices obliquely truncate with wide membranous margins; intervals densely pubescent and punctuated; lateral edges narrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFF9647F4784293AFC51FBE5" blockId="6.[151,1437,698,1604]" box="[197,967,1098,1124]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F4784293AFEB6FBE5" bold="true" box="[197,288,1098,1124]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Venter.</emphasis>
