<subSubSection id="C30A949AFFF9647F4784284AFCF2F9C5" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAFC711FFF9647F4784284AFCF2F9C5" blockId="6.[151,1437,698,1604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F4784284AFEA8FAD5" bold="true" box="[197,318,1338,1364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
With slightly emarginate margin between anterior angles of labrum, rounded anterior angles of pronotum and slender ligula, 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFF9647F46B12813FD0CFAFD" box="[496,666,1379,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Helluodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taprobanae">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F46B12813FD0CFAFD" box="[496,666,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">H. taprobanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFF9647F44362813FBAEFAFD" authority="Sabu &amp; Abhitha &amp; Zhao, 2008" authorityName="Sabu &amp; Abhitha &amp; Zhao" authorityYear="2008" box="[887,1080,1379,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Helluodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devagiriensis" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F44362813FBAEFAFD" box="[887,1080,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">H. devagiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F437E2812FBECFAFD" bold="true" box="[1087,1146,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A257A678FFF9647F437E2812FBECFAFD" box="[1087,1146,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differs from the latter in the absence of dentation on the anterior margin of labrum, maxillary palpomere 4 roundly dilated from middle to apex and roundly narrowed at apex, and in more densely punctuate pronotal disc. Although females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFF9647F47F928ABFEF2FA75" box="[184,356,1499,1524]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Helluodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taprobanae">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F47F928ABFEF2FA75" box="[184,356,1499,1524]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">H. taprobanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not known, we predict that the venter of the female will not have paramedial setae on segments 3 and 4 and that this will be a sexually dimorphic character similar to that found in all species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFF9647F47A22B5BFECCF9C5" box="[227,346,1579,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Helluodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9641B03FFF9647F47A22B5BFECCF9C5" box="[227,346,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="36">Helluodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BC92FFF9647F468E2B5AFD1BF9C5" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1863" box="[463,653,1578,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Physocrotaphini">Physocrotaphini</taxonomicName>
examined to date.
</paragraph>
